ULL,NULL,'3h',NULL,NULL,'size',0,'HTML'),(1411,'NPath Complexity','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.metrics.NPathComplexityCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/NPathComplexity','checkstyle','Checks the npath complexity of a method against a specified limit (default = 200). The NPATH metric computes the number of possible execution paths through a function. It takes into account the nesting of conditional statements and multi-part boolean expressions (e.g., A && B, C || D, etc.).',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:26:59','2016-03-15 10:26:59',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,51,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1h',NULL,NULL,'size',0,'HTML'),(1412,'Right Curly','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.blocks.RightCurlyCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/RightCurly','checkstyle','Checks the placement of right curly braces.\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:RightCurlyBraceStartLineCheck} instead.\n</p>',1,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:26:59','2016-03-15 10:26:59',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2min',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1413,'Abstract Class Name','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.naming.AbstractClassNameCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/AbstractClassName','checkstyle','<p>\nChecks that abstract class names conform to the specified format\n</p>\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S00118} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:26:59','2016-03-15 10:26:59',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,'naming',0,'HTML'),(1414,'Final Parameters','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.FinalParametersCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/FinalParameters','checkstyle','Check that method/constructor/catch/foreach parameters are final.\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S1226} instead.\n</p>',1,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,39,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5min',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1415,'Overload Methods Declaration Order','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.OverloadMethodsDeclarationOrderCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/OverloadMethodsDeclarationOrder','checkstyle','Checks that overload methods are grouped together.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1416,'Mutable Exception','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.design.MutableExceptionCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/MutableException','checkstyle','Ensures that exceptions (defined as any class name conforming to some regular expression) are immutable.\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S1165} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,40,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'30min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1417,'Member name','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.naming.MemberNameCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/MemberName','checkstyle','<p>\nChecks that name of non-static fields conform to the specified format\n</p>\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S00116} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'20min',NULL,NULL,'naming',1,'HTML'),(1418,'Trailing Comment','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.TrailingCommentCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/TrailingComment','checkstyle','<p>\n  The check to ensure that requires that comments be the only thing on a line. For the case of // comments that means that the only thing that should precede it is whitespace. It\n  doesn\'t check comments if they do not end line, i.e. it accept the following: Thread.sleep( 10 &lt;some comment here&gt; ); Format property is intended to deal with the \"} //\n  while\" example.\n</p>\n<p>\n  Rationale: Steve McConnel in \"Code Complete\" suggests that endline comments are a bad practice. An end line comment would be one that is on the same line as actual code. For\n  example:\n</p>\n<pre>\n  <code>\n    a = b + c; // Some insightful comment\n    d = e / f; // Another comment for this line\n  </code>\n</pre>\n\n<p>\n  Quoting \"Code Complete\" for the justfication:\n</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>\"The comments have to be aligned so that they do not interfere with the visual structure of the code. If you don\'t align them neatly, they\'ll make your listing look like it\'s\n    been through a washing machine.\"\n  </li>\n  <li>\"Endline comments tend to be hard to format...It takes time to align them. Such time is not spent learning more about the code; it\'s dedicated solely to the tedious task of\n    pressing the spacebar or tab key.\"\n  </li>\n  <li>\"Endline comments are also hard to maintain. If the code on any line containing an endline comment grows, it bumps the comment farther out, and all the other endline comments\n    will have to bumped out to match. Styles that are hard to maintain aren\'t maintained....\"\n  </li>\n  <li>\"Endline comments also tend to be cryptic. The right side of the line doesn\'t offer much room and the desire to keep the comment on one line means the comment must be short.\n    Work\n    then goes into making the line as short as possible instead of as clear as possible. The comment usually ends up as cryptic as possible....\"\n  </li>\n  <li>\"A systemic problem with endline comments is that it\'s hard to write a meaningful comment for one line of code. Most endline comments just repeat the line of code, which\n    hurts\n    more than it helps.\"\n  </li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  His comments on being hard to maintain when the size of the line changes are even more important in the age of automated refactorings.\n</p>\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:TrailingCommentCheck} instead.\n</p>',1,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1419,'Array Trailing Comma','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.ArrayTrailingCommaCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/ArrayTrailingComma','checkstyle','Checks if array initialization contains optional trailing comma.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1420,'Class Type(Generic) Parameter Name','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.naming.ClassTypeParameterNameCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/ClassTypeParameterName','checkstyle','Checks that class parameter names conform to the specified format\n\n<p>\nThe following code snippet illustrates this rule for format \"^[A-Z]$\":\n</p>\n<pre>\nclass Something&lt;type&gt; { // Non-compliant\n}\n\nclass Something&lt;T&gt; { // Compliant\n}\n</pre>\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S00119} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,'naming',0,'HTML'),(1421,'Regexp Singleline','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.regexp.RegexpSinglelineCheck','Checker/RegexpSingleline','checkstyle','<p> A check for detecting single lines that match a supplied regular expression. Works with any file type. Rationale: This check can be used to prototype checks and to find common bad practice such as calling ex.printStacktrace(), System.out.println(), System.exit(), etc.</p>',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1422,'Array Type Style','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.ArrayTypeStyleCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/ArrayTypeStyle','checkstyle','Checks the style of array type definitions. Some like Java-style: public static void main(String[] args) and some like C-style: public static void main(String args[])\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S1197} instead.\n</p>',1,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1423,'Left Curly','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.blocks.LeftCurlyCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/LeftCurly','checkstyle','Checks for the placement of left curly braces for code blocks. The policy to verify is specified using property option. Policies <code>eol</code> and <code>nlow</code> take into account property maxLineLength.\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:LeftCurlyBraceStartLineCheck} and {rule:squid:LeftCurlyBraceEndLineCheck} instead.\n</p>',1,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1min',NULL,NULL,'formatting',1,'HTML'),(1424,'Parameter Name','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.naming.ParameterNameCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/ParameterName','checkstyle','Checks that parameter names conform to the specified format\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S00117} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1425,'Whitespace Around','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.whitespace.WhitespaceAroundCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/WhitespaceAround','checkstyle','Checks that a token is surrounded by whitespace.',1,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2min',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1426,'Design For Extension','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.design.DesignForExtensionCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/DesignForExtension','checkstyle','Checks that classes are designed for inheritance.',1,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,33,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1h',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1427,'Javadoc Method','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.javadoc.JavadocMethodCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/JavadocMethod','checkstyle','Checks the Javadoc of a method or constructor. By default, does not check for unused throws.\n    To allow documented java.lang.RuntimeExceptions that are not declared, set property allowUndeclaredRTE to true.\n    The scope to verify is specified using the Scope class and defaults to Scope.PRIVATE.\n    To verify another scope, set property scope to a different scope.\n\n    <br><br>Error messages about parameters and type parameters for which no param tags are present can be suppressed by defining property allowMissingParamTags.\n    Error messages about exceptions which are declared to be thrown, but for which no throws tag is present can be suppressed by defining property allowMissingThrowsTags.\n    Error messages about methods which return non-void but for which no return tag is present can be suppressed by defining property allowMissingReturnTag.\n\n    <br><br>Javadoc is not required on a method that is tagged with the @Override annotation.\n    However under Java 5 it is not possible to mark a method required for an interface (this was corrected under Java 6).\n    Hence Checkstyle supports using the convention of using a single {@inheritDoc} tag instead of all the other tags.\n\n    <br><br>Note that only inheritable items will allow the {@inheritDoc} tag to be used in place of comments.\n    Static methods at all visibilities, private non-static methods and constructors are not inheritable.\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:UndocumentedApi} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'30min',NULL,NULL,'comment',1,'HTML'),(1428,'Generic Whitespace','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.whitespace.GenericWhitespaceCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/GenericWhitespace','checkstyle','<p>Checks that the whitespace around the Generic tokens < and >  is correct to the typical convention. The convention is not configurable.</p>\n<p>\nFor example the following is legal:\n</p>\n<pre>\n  List<Integer> x = new ArrayList<Integer>();\n  List<List<Integer>> y = new ArrayList<List<Integer>>();\n</pre>\n<p>\nBut the following example is not:\n</p>\n<pre>\n  List < Integer > x = new ArrayList < Integer > ();\n  List < List < Integer > > y = new ArrayList < List < Integer > > ();\n</pre>',1,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1429,'Class Fan Out Complexity','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.metrics.ClassFanOutComplexityCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/ClassFanOutComplexity','checkstyle','The number of other classes a given class relies on.\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S1200} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,33,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2h',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1430,'Operator Wrap','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.whitespace.OperatorWrapCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/OperatorWrap','checkstyle','Checks the policy on how to wrap lines on operators.',1,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5min',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1431,'JavaNCSS','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.metrics.JavaNCSSCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/JavaNCSS','checkstyle','Determines complexity of methods, classes and files by counting the Non Commenting Source Statements (NCSS). This check adheres to the  specification for the JavaNCSS-Tool  written by Chr. Clemens Lee.\nRougly said the NCSS metric is calculated by counting the source lines which are not comments, (nearly) equivalent to counting the semicolons and opening curly braces.\nThe NCSS for a class is summarized from the NCSS of all its methods, the NCSS of its nested classes and the number of member variable declarations.\nThe NCSS for a file is summarized from the ncss of all its top level classes, the number of imports and the package declaration.\n<br>\nRationale: Too large methods and classes are hard to read and costly to maintain. A large NCSS number often means that a method or class has too many responsabilities and/or functionalities which should be decomposed into smaller units.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'3h',NULL,NULL,'size',0,'HTML'),(1432,'Visibility Modifier','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.design.VisibilityModifierCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/VisibilityModifier','checkstyle','Checks visibility of class members. Only static final members may be public; other class members must be private unless property protectedAllowed or packageAllowed is set.\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:ClassVariableVisibilityCheck} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:00','2016-03-15 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,33,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1433,'Magic Number','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.MagicNumberCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/MagicNumber','checkstyle','Checks for magic numbers.\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S109} instead.\n</p>',1,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,35,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5min',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1434,'Javadoc Tag Continuation Indentation','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.javadoc.JavadocTagContinuationIndentationCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/JavadocTagContinuationIndentation','checkstyle','Checks the indentation of the continuation lines in at-clauses.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1435,'Need Braces','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.blocks.NeedBracesCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/NeedBraces','checkstyle','<p>\nChecks for braces around code blocks.\n</p>\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S00121} instead.\n</p>',1,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,36,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,'convention',1,'HTML'),(1436,'Redundant Modifier','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.modifier.RedundantModifierCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/RedundantModifier','checkstyle','Checks for redundant modifiers in interface and annotation definitions.',1,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2min',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1437,'Illegal Import','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.imports.IllegalImportCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/IllegalImport','checkstyle','Checks for imports from a set of illegal packages, like sun.*\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S1191} or {rule:squid:ArchitecturalConstraint} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,38,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1h',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1438,'Illegal Token Text','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.IllegalTokenTextCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/IllegalTokenText','checkstyle','Checks for illegal token text.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'30min',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1439,'Whitespace After','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.whitespace.WhitespaceAfterCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/WhitespaceAfter','checkstyle','Checks that a token is followed by whitespace, with the exception that it does not check for whitespace after the semicolon of an empty for iterator.',1,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2min',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1440,'Class Data Abstraction Coupling','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.metrics.ClassDataAbstractionCouplingCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/ClassDataAbstractionCoupling','checkstyle','This metric measures the number of instantiations of other classes within the given class.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,33,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1h',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1441,'Javadoc summary','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.javadoc.SummaryJavadocCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/SummaryJavadocCheck','checkstyle','Checks that Javadoc summary sentence does not contain phrases that are not recommended to use.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1442,'Regexp Multiline','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.regexp.RegexpMultilineCheck','Checker/RegexpMultiline','checkstyle','<p>A check for detecting that matches across multiple lines. Rationale: This check can be used to when the regular expression can be span multiple lines.</p>',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1443,'Regexp Header','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.header.RegexpHeaderCheck','Checker/RegexpHeader','checkstyle','<p>Checks the header of a source file against a header that contains a regular expression for each line of the source header.</p>\n	<p>Rationale: In some projects checking against a fixed header is not sufficient, e.g. the header might require a copyright line where the year information is not static. For example, consider the following header:</p>\n<pre>\n	line  1: ^/{71}$\n	line  2: ^// checkstyle:$\n	line  3: ^// Checks Java source code for adherence to a set of rules\\.$\n	line  4: ^// Copyright \\(C\\) \\d\\d\\d\\d  Oliver Burn$\n	line  5: ^// Last modification by \\$Author.*\\$$\n	line  6: ^/{71}$\n	line  7:\n	line  8: ^package\n	line  9:\n	line 10: ^import\n	line 11:\n	line 12: ^/\\*\\*\n	line 13: ^ \\*([^/]|$)\n	line 14: ^ \\*/\n</pre>\n<p>Lines 1 and 6 demonstrate a more compact notation for 71 \'/\' characters. Line 4 enforces that the copyright notice includes a four digit year. Line 5 is an example how to enforce revision control keywords in a file header. Lines 12-14 is a template for javadoc (line 13 is so complicated to remove conflict with and of javadoc comment).</p>\n<p>Different programming languages have different comment syntax rules, but all of them start a comment with a non-word character. Hence you can often use the non-word character class to abstract away the concrete comment syntax and allow checking the header for different languages with a single header definition. For example, consider the following header specification (note that this is not the full Apache license header):</p>\n<pre>\n	line 1: ^#!\n	line 2: ^<\\?xml.*>$\n	line 3: ^\\W*$\n	line 4: ^\\W*Copyright 2006 The Apache Software Foundation or its licensors, as applicable\\.$\n	line 5: ^\\W*Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2\\.0 \\(the \"License\"\\);$\n	line 6: ^\\W*$\n</pre>\n<p>Lines 1 and 2 leave room for technical header lines, e.g. the \"#!/bin/sh\" line in Unix shell scripts, or the xml file header of XML files. Set the multiline property to \"1, 2\" so these lines can be ignored for file types where they do no apply. Lines 3 through 6 define the actual header content. Note how lines 2, 4 and 5 use escapes for characters that have special regexp semantics.</p>\n<p>Note: ignoreLines property has been removed from this check to simplify it. To make some line optional use \"^.*$\" regexp for this line. </p>',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1444,'Equals Avoid Null','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.EqualsAvoidNullCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/EqualsAvoidNull','checkstyle','<p>Checks that any combination of String literals with optional assignment is on the left side of an equals() comparison.</p>\n<p>Rationale: Calling the equals() method on String literals will avoid a potential NullPointerException. Also, it is pretty common to see null check right before equals comparisons which is not necessary in the below example.</p>\n<p>For example:\n<pre>\n  String nullString = null;\n  nullString.equals(\"My_Sweet_String\");\n</pre>\n</p>\n\n<p>\nshould be refactored to:\n<pre>\n  String nullString = null;\n  \"My_Sweet_String\".equals(nullString);\n</pre>\n</p>\n<p>Limitations: If the equals method is overridden or a covariant equals method is defined and the implementation is incorrect (where s.equals(t) does not return the same result as t.equals(s)) then rearranging the called on object and parameter may have unexpected results.</p>\n<p>Java\'s Autoboxing feature has an affect on how this check is implemented. Pre Java 5 all IDENT + IDENT object concatenations would not cause a NullPointerException even if null. Those situations could have been included in this check. They would simply act as if they surrounded by String.valueof() which would concatenate the String null.</p>\n<p>The following example will cause a NullPointerException as a result of what autoboxing does.</p>\n<pre>\n  Integer i = null, j = null;\n  String number = \"5\"\n  number.equals(i + j);\n</pre>\n<p>Since, it is difficult to determine what kind of Object is being concatenated all ident concatenation is considered unsafe.</p>\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S1132} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,41,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1445,'Comments Indentation','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.indentation.CommentsIndentationCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/CommentsIndentation','checkstyle','<p>Controls the indentation between comments and surrounding code. Comments are indented at the same level as the surrounding code. Detailed info about such convention can be found <a href=\"http://checkstyle.sourceforge.net/reports/google-java-style.html#s4.8.6.1-block-comment-style\">here</a></p>',1,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'LINEAR',NULL,'5min',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1446,'Nested If Depth','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.NestedIfDepthCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/NestedIfDepth','checkstyle','Restricts nested if-else blocks to a specified depth (default = 1).\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S134} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,36,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'20min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1447,'Missing Constructor','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.MissingCtorCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/MissingCtor','checkstyle','Checks that classes (except abstract one) define a constructor and don\'t rely on the default one.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,39,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'30min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1448,'Regexp','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.RegexpCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/Regexp','checkstyle','A check that makes sure that a specified pattern exists (or not) in the file.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1449,'Non Empty At-clause Description','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.javadoc.NonEmptyAtclauseDescriptionCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/NonEmptyAtclauseDescription','checkstyle','Checks that the at-clause tag is followed by description.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1450,'Javadoc Style','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.javadoc.JavadocStyleCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/JavadocStyle','checkstyle','Validates Javadoc comments to help ensure they are well formed. The following checks are performed:\n    <ul>\n      <li>Ensures the first sentence ends with proper punctuation (That is a period, question mark, or exclamation mark, by default). \n      Javadoc automatically places the first sentence in the method summary table and index. With out proper punctuation the Javadoc may be malformed. \n      All items eligible for the {@inheritDoc} tag are exempt from this requirement.</li>\n      <li>Check text for Javadoc statements that do not have any description. \n      This includes both completely empty Javadoc, and Javadoc with only tags such as @param and @return.</li>\n      <li>Check text for incomplete HTML tags. Verifies that HTML tags have corresponding end tags and issues an \"Unclosed HTML tag found:\" error if not. \n      An \"Extra HTML tag found:\" error is issued if an end tag is found without a previous open tag.</li>\n      <li>Check that a package Javadoc comment is well-formed (as described above) and NOT missing from any package-info.java files.</li>\n      <li>Check for allowed HTML tags. The list of allowed HTML tags is \"a\", \"abbr\", \"acronym\", \"address\", \"area\", \"b\", \n      \"bdo\", \"big\", \"blockquote\", \"br\", \"caption\", \"cite\", \"code\", \"colgroup\", \"del\", \"div\", \"dfn\", \"dl\", \"em\", \"fieldset\", \n      \"h1\" to \"h6\", \"hr\", \"i\", \"img\", \"ins\", \"kbd\", \"li\", \"ol\", \"p\", \"pre\", \"q\", \"samp\", \"small\", \"span\", \"strong\", \n      \"sub\", \"sup\", \"table\", \"tbody\", \"td\", \"tfoot\", \"th\", \"thread\", \"tr\", \"tt\", \"ul\"</li>\n    </ul>',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'30min',NULL,NULL,'comment',1,'HTML'),(1451,'Empty catch block','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.blocks.EmptyCatchBlockCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/EmptyCatchBlockCheck','checkstyle','Checks for empty catch blocks. There are two options to make validation more precise (by default Check allows empty catch block with any comment inside)',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:01','2016-03-15 10:27:01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,43,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1452,'Outer Type Number','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.sizes.OuterTypeNumberCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/OuterTypeNumber','checkstyle','<p> Checks for the number of types declared at the outer (or root) level in a file. Rationale: It is considered good practice to only define one outer type per file.</p>',1,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1453,'Write Tag','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.javadoc.WriteTagCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/WriteTag','checkstyle','Outputs a JavaDoc tag as information. Can be used e.g. with the stylesheets that sort the report by author name. To define the format for a tag, set property tagFormat to a regular expression. This check uses two different severity levels. The normal one is used for reporting when the tag is missing. The additional one (tagSeverity) is used for the level of reporting when the tag exists.',1,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'30min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1454,'Header','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.header.HeaderCheck','Checker/Header','checkstyle','<p>Checks that a source file begins with a specified header. Property headerFile specifies a file that contains the required header. Alternatively, the header specification can be set directly in the header property without the need for an external file.</p>\n<p>Property ignoreLines specifies the line numbers to ignore when matching lines in a header file. This property is very useful for supporting headers that contain copyright dates. For example, consider the following header:</p>\n<pre>\n	line 1: ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////\n	line 2: // checkstyle:\n	line 3: // Checks Java source code for adherence to a set of rules.\n	line 4: // Copyright (C) 2002  Oliver Burn\n	line 5: ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////\n</pre>\n<p>Since the year information will change over time, you can tell Checkstyle to ignore line 4 by setting property ignoreLines to 4.</p>',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,22,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1455,'Interface Is Type','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.design.InterfaceIsTypeCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/InterfaceIsType','checkstyle','Implements Bloch, Effective Java, Item 17 - Use Interfaces only to define types.  According to Bloch, an interface should describe a type. It is therefore inappropriate to define an interface that does not contain any methods but only constants. The Standard class javax.swing.SwingConstants is an example of a class that would be flagged by this check. The check can be configured to also disallow marker interfaces like java.io.Serializable, that do not contain methods or constants at all.\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S1214} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,35,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'20min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1456,'Method Param Pad','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.whitespace.MethodParamPadCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/MethodParamPad','checkstyle','Checks the padding between the identifier of a method definition, constructor definition, method call, or constructor invocation; and the left parenthesis of the parameter list.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1min',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1457,'Avoid Static Import','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.imports.AvoidStaticImportCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/AvoidStaticImport','checkstyle','<p> Checks that there are no static import statements. Rationale: Importing static members can lead to naming conflicts between class\' members. It may lead to poor code readability since it may no longer be clear what class a member resides in (without looking at the import statement).</p>',1,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,38,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'15min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1458,'Paren Pad','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.whitespace.ParenPadCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/ParenPad','checkstyle','Checks the padding of parentheses; that is whether a space is required after a left parenthesis and before a right parenthesis, or such spaces are forbidden, with the exception that it does not check for padding of the right parenthesis at an empty for iterator.',1,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2min',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1459,'Method Type(Generic) Parameter Name','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.naming.MethodTypeParameterNameCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/MethodTypeParameterName','checkstyle','Checks that method type parameter names conform to the specified format\n\n<p>\nThe following code snippet illustrates this rule for format \"^[A-Z]$\":\n</p>\n<pre>\npublic &lt;type&gt; boolean containsAll(Collection&lt;type&gt; c) { // Non-compliant\n  return null;\n}\n\npublic &lt;T&gt; boolean containsAll(Collection&lt;T&gt; c) { // Compliant\n}\n</pre>\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S00119} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,'naming',0,'HTML'),(1460,'Nested For Depth','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.NestedForDepthCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/NestedForDepth','checkstyle','Restricts nested for blocks to a specified depth.\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S134} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,36,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'20min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1461,'Hidden Field','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.HiddenFieldCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/HiddenField','checkstyle','Checks that a local variable or a parameter does not shadow a field that is defined in the same class.\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:HiddenFieldCheck} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,39,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'30min',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1462,'Final Local Variable','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.FinalLocalVariableCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/FinalLocalVariable','checkstyle','Ensures that local variables that never get their values changed, must be declared final.',1,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,39,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1463,'Missing Override','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.annotation.MissingOverrideCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/MissingOverride','checkstyle','Verifies that the java.lang.Override annotation is present when the {@inheritDoc} javadoc tag is present.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,38,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1464,'Outer Type Filename','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.OuterTypeFilenameCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/OuterTypeFilename','checkstyle','Checks that the outer type name and the file name match. For example, the class Foo must be in a file named Foo.java.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1465,'Boolean Expression Complexity','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.metrics.BooleanExpressionComplexityCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/BooleanExpressionComplexity','checkstyle','Restricts nested boolean operators (&&, || and ^) to a specified depth (default = 3).\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S1067} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'30min',NULL,NULL,'size',1,'HTML'),(1466,'No Whitespace Before','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.whitespace.NoWhitespaceBeforeCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/NoWhitespaceBefore','checkstyle','Checks that there is no whitespace before a token.',1,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2min',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1467,'Illegal Throws','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.IllegalThrowsCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/IllegalThrows','checkstyle','Throwing java.lang.Error or java.lang.RuntimeException is almost never acceptable.\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S00112} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,40,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'20min',NULL,NULL,'error-handling',0,'HTML'),(1468,'Executable Statement Count','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.sizes.ExecutableStatementCountCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/ExecutableStatementCount','checkstyle','Restricts the number of executable statements to a specified limit (default = 30).',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1h',NULL,NULL,'size',1,'HTML'),(1469,'Local Final Variable Name','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.naming.LocalFinalVariableNameCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/LocalFinalVariableName','checkstyle','Checks that local final variable names, including catch parameters, conform to the specified format\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S00117} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1470,'Import Order','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.imports.ImportOrderCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/ImportOrder','checkstyle','Checks the ordering/grouping of imports. Features are:<ul>\n    <li>groups imports: ensures that groups of imports come in a specific order (e.g., java. comes first, javax. comes second, then everything else)</li>\n    <li>adds a separation between groups : ensures that a blank line sit between each group</li>\n    <li>sorts imports inside each group: ensures that imports within each group are in lexicographic order</li>\n    <li>sorts according to case: ensures that the comparison between imports is case sensitive</li>\n    <li>groups static imports: ensures the relative order between regular imports and static imports</li>\n    </ul>',1,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1471,'Import Control','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.imports.ImportControlCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/ImportControl','checkstyle','<p>Controls what can be imported in each package.\nUseful for ensuring that application layering rules are not violated, especially on large projects.</p>\n\n<p>The DTD for a import control XML document is at <a href=\"http://www.puppycrawl.com/dtds/import_control_1_1.dtd\"\ntarget=\"_blank\">http://www.puppycrawl.com/dtds/import_control_1_1.dtd</a>. It contains documentation on each of the\nelements and attributes.</p>\n\n<p>The check validates a XML document when it loads the document. To validate against the above DTD, include the\nfollowing document type declaration in your XML document:</p>\n\n<pre>&lt;!DOCTYPE import-control PUBLIC\n    \"-//Puppy Crawl//DTD Import Control 1.1//EN\"\n    \"http://www.puppycrawl.com/dtds/import_control_1_1.dtd\"&gt;</pre>\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:ArchitecturalConstraint} instead.\n</p>',4,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1472,'Illegal Catch','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.IllegalCatchCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/IllegalCatch','checkstyle','Catching java.lang.Exception, java.lang.Error or java.lang.RuntimeException is almost never acceptable.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,41,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'15min',NULL,NULL,'error-handling',0,'HTML'),(1473,'Simplify Boolean Return','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.SimplifyBooleanReturnCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/SimplifyBooleanReturn','checkstyle','Checks for overly complicated boolean return statements.\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S1126} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1474,'Annotation Use Style','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.annotation.AnnotationUseStyleCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/AnnotationUseStyle','checkstyle','Controls the style with the usage of annotations.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'15min',NULL,NULL,'formatting',0,'HTML'),(1475,'Annotation Location','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.annotation.AnnotationLocationCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/AnnotationLocation','checkstyle','<p>Check location of annotation on language elements. By default, Check enforce to locate annotations immetiately after documentation block and before target element, annotation should be located on separate line from target element.</p>\n\n<p>Example:</p>\n\n<pre>\n@Override\n@Nullable\npublic String getNameIfPresent() { ... }\n</pre>',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1476,'Method Count','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.sizes.MethodCountCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/MethodCount','checkstyle','Checks the number of methods declared in each type. This includes the number of each scope (private, package, protected and public) as well as an overall total.',2,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1h',NULL,NULL,'size',0,'HTML'),(1477,'Missing Switch Default','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.MissingSwitchDefaultCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/MissingSwitchDefault','checkstyle','Checks that switch statement has default clause.\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:SwitchLastCaseIsDefaultCheck} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,43,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'30min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1478,'Multiple String Literals','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.MultipleStringLiteralsCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/MultipleStringLiterals','checkstyle','Checks for multiple occurrences of the same string literal within a single file. Code duplication makes maintenance more difficult, so it can be better to replace the multiple occurrences with a constant.\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S1192} instead.\n</p>',2,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,35,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'HTML'),(1479,'Package Annotation','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.annotation.PackageAnnotationCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/PackageAnnotation','checkstyle','<p>This check makes sure that all package annotations are in the package-info.java file.</p>\n<p>According to the Java JLS 3rd ed.</p>\n<p>The JLS does not enforce the placement of package annotations. This placement may vary based on implementation. The JLS does highly recommend that all package annotations are placed in the package-info.java file. See <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/docs/books/jls/third_edition/html/j3TOC.html\">Java Language specification, sections 7.4.1.1</a>.</p>',1,NULL,'READY','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10min',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HTML'),(1480,'Equals Hash Code','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.EqualsHashCodeCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/EqualsHashCode','checkstyle','Checks that classes that override equals() also override hashCode().\n\n<p>\nThis rule is deprecated, use {rule:squid:S1206} instead.\n</p>',3,NULL,'DEPRECATED','java','2016-03-15 10:27:02','2016-03-15 10:27:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,42,NULL,'CONSTANT_ISSUE',NULL,NULL,NULL,'30min',NULL,NULL,'bug',0,'HTML'),(1481,'Illegal Instantiation','com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.coding.IllegalInstantiationCheck','Checker/TreeWalker/IllegalInstantiation','checkstyle','Checks for illegal instantiations where a factory method is preferred. Depending on the project, for some classes it might be preferable to create instances through